  "name": "Multimodal Analgesia - Medication Query (Multi-Class Union)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find patients on any analgesic class — opioid (oxycodone), NSAID (ibuprofen), or acetaminophen. Per PheKB Stanford algorithm, multimodal analgesia is the combination at discharge — but a union query identifies the at-risk pool.",
